definitions.definition: Heartwood from trees of genus Aquilaria , especially Aquilaria malaccensis (syn. A. agallocha ), infected with mold ( Phialophora parasitica ), which produce an aromatic resin in response to this infestation.

main_definition: Heartwood from trees of genus Aquilaria , especially Aquilaria malaccensis (syn. A. agallocha ), infected with mold ( Phialophora parasitica ), which produce an aromatic resin in response to this infestation.
